.TH SUSEDIALOG 1 "April 2026" "susedialog" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
susedialog \- openSUSE-branded terminal dialog shim
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B susedialog
[\fIcommon-options\fR]
.I widget
[\fIwidget-options\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B susedialog
is a Bubble Tea-based compatibility shim for a subset of
.BR dialog (1)
widgets, designed for openSUSE system tooling such as
.B jeos-firstboot
and
.BR opensuse-migration-tool .
.PP
Like
.BR dialog ,
the UI is drawn on standard output and the selected value(s) are written to
standard error (or the file descriptor given by
.BR --output-fd ).
A non-zero exit status signals cancellation.
.PP
Screen clearing between dialogs is
.B enabled by default
(equivalent to always passing
.B --clear
to
.BR dialog ).
.SH WIDGETS
.TP
.BI "--msgbox " "text height width"
Display a message box with an
.B OK
button.
Returns 0 when dismissed.
.TP
.BI "--infobox " "text height width"
Display a non-interactive informational message and exit immediately with
status 0.
.TP
.BI "--textbox " "file height width"
Display the contents of
.I file
in a scrollable box.
Press
.B Enter
or click
.B Continue
to dismiss.
.TP
.BI "--yesno " "text height width"
Display a yes/no question.
Returns 0 for Yes, 1 for No.
.TP
.BI "--inputbox " "text height width"
Prompt the user for a single line of text.
The entered value is written to the output file descriptor.
.TP
.BI "--passwordbox " "text height width"
Like
.B --inputbox
but input is masked with asterisks.
The entered value is written to the output file descriptor.
.TP
.BI "--menu " "text height width list-height tag label [tag label] ..."
Display a single-selection menu.
Writes the selected
.I tag
to the output file descriptor.
.TP
.BI "--checklist " "text height width list-height tag label state [tag label state] ..."
Display a multi-selection checklist.
.I state
is
.B on
or
.BR off .
Writes a space-separated quoted list of selected tags to the output file descriptor.
.TP
.BI "--form " "text height width form-height label y x init y x flen ilen [...]"
Display an editable form with labelled fields.
Field positions and lengths are accepted for
.BR dialog (1)
compatibility but layout is managed automatically.
Writes field values separated by newlines to the output file descriptor.
.TP
.BI "--mixedform " "text height width form-height label y x init y x flen ilen type [...]"
Like
.B --form
but each field has an additional
.I type
argument:
.B 0
normal,
.B 1
password (masked),
.B 2
read-only label.
.TP
.BI "--progress " "text height width [percent]"
Display a progress bar.
If
.I percent
is given the bar is set to that value; otherwise it reads percentages from
standard input.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "--title " title
Set the dialog title.
.TP
.BI "--backtitle " backtitle
Set the background title (displayed at the top of the screen).
.TP
.BI "--ok-label " label
Override the label of the OK/Yes button (default:
.BR OK ).
.TP
.BI "--cancel-label " label
Override the label of the Cancel/No button.
.TP
.BI "--exit-label " label
Override the label of the Exit button (default:
.BR Exit ).
.TP
.BI "--output-fd " fd
Write output to file descriptor
.I fd
instead of standard error.
.TP
.BI "--default-item " tag
Pre-select
.I tag
in a menu or checklist.
.TP
.BI "--theme " name
Select a named color theme.
Built-in themes include
.B opensuse
and
.BR high-contrast .
.TP
.B --clear
Clear the screen before rendering the next dialog.
This is the default behavior; the flag is accepted for
.BR dialog (1)
compatibility.
.TP
.B --insecure
Accepted for compatibility.
Password fields are always masked regardless of this flag.
.TP
.B --no-nl-expand
Do not expand
.B \\n
escape sequences in text strings.
.TP
.B --no-collapse
Accepted for
.BR dialog (1)
compatibility; has no effect.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The user confirmed or selected a value (Yes, OK, Continue).
.TP
.B 1
The user cancelled (No, Cancel, ESC).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SUSEDIALOG_DEBUG_KEYS
When set to
.BR 1 ,
received key names are printed to standard error while a dialog is running.
Useful for debugging key-handling issues.
.TP
.B SUSEDIALOG_THEME
Selects the theme when
.B --theme
is not specified.
.TP
.B SUSEDIALOG_THEME_TOGGLE_KEY
Sets the key binding used to toggle between
.B opensuse
and
.B high-contrast
themes while a dialog is open.
Default is
.BR ctrl+t .
.PP
Theme resolution order is:
.B --theme
option,
.B SUSEDIALOG_THEME
environment variable,
.I ~/.config/susedialog/config
(or
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/susedialog/config ),
then
.IR /etc/susedialog/config .
.PP
The toggle shortcut can be set in config files with
.B theme_toggle_key
or via
.BR SUSEDIALOG_THEME_TOGGLE_KEY .
.SH EXAMPLES
Display a simple message:
.PP
.RS
.EX
susedialog --title "Hello" --msgbox "Installation complete." 10 50
.EE
.RE
.PP
Prompt the user to choose a migration target:
.PP
.RS
.EX
CHOICE=$(susedialog --title "Migration" \\
  --menu "Select target:" 20 60 10 \\
  "15.6" "openSUSE Leap 15.6" \\
  "16.0" "openSUSE Leap 16.0" \\
  2>&1 >/dev/tty) || exit 1
.EE
.RE
.PP
Collect user credentials:
.PP
.RS
.EX
PASS=$(susedialog --title "Auth" \\
  --passwordbox "Enter password:" 10 50 \\
  2>&1 >/dev/tty)
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dialog (1)
.SH AUTHORS
susedialog was written by the openSUSE community.
